SR-11
Sunroof Assembly
SUNROOF/T-TOP/CONVERTIBLE TOP (SUNROOF)
5. Sunroof Assembly
A: REMOVAL
1) Disconnect the ground cable from battery. <Ref. to NT-5, BATTERY, NOTE, Note.>
NOTE:
Completely close the lid assembly - sunroof, then disconnect the ground cable.
For models other than STI model, disconnect the ground terminal from battery sensor.
2) Remove the lid assembly - sunroof.
CAUTION:
Be careful not to damage the lid assembly - sunroof.
(1) Completely close the lid assembly - sunroof, and open the sunshade assembly.
(2) Remove the lid assembly - sunroof.
Preparation tool:
TORX
T25
3) Remove the trim panel - roof assembly. <Ref. to EI-99, REMOVAL, Roof Trim.>
4) Remove the bracket - assist rail.
5) Disconnect the connector of the motor assembly - sunroof.

SR-00196

6) Remove the rail assembly - sunroof.
(1) Remove the drain tube - sunroof.
(2) Remove the bolts and then remove the sunroof bracket.

(3) Remove the bolts, then remove the rail assembly.
B: INSTALLATION
CAUTION:
Be careful not to snag the harness.
1) Install the sunroof bracket and the rail assembly - sunroof.
Tightening torque:
6 Nm (0.6 kgf-m, 4.4 ft-lb)
2) Connect the harness connector of the drain tube - sunroof and the motor assembly.
CAUTION:
Insert the four drain tubes 15 mm (0.59 in) or more into the drain pipes (A).

3) Install the bracket - assist rail.
Tightening torque:
7.5 Nm (0.8 kgf-m, 5.5 ft-lb)
4) Install the trim panel - roof assembly. <Ref. to EI-102, INSTALLATION, Roof Trim.>
5) Using a new TORX
bolt, install the lid assembly - sunroof.
Tightening torque:
4.5 Nm (0.5 kgf-m, 3.3 ft-lb)
C: DISASSEMBLY
1) Remove the screw and remove the sunroof motor.
2) Remove the stopper rubber and pull out the sunshade assembly from the rail assembly - sunroof.

3) Disconnect the claws and then remove the drain holder.
4) Remove the screw and pull out the cable assembly from the rail assembly - sunroof.
D: ASSEMBLY
1) Insert the cable assembly into the rail assembly - sunroof.
2) Install the drain holder.
3) Insert the sunshade assembly into the rail assembly - sunroof, and install the stopper rubber.
4) Install the sunroof motor.
